<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="9May1937"><font color="red">9 May 1937</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Viscount Carlow): And finally. Faber and Faber have sent me a bundle of proofs of &lsquo;Work in Progress&rsquo; and as their printer is nearing Miss Storiella could you send to my friend T.S. Eliot of that firm a list of the few corrections and additions to the text they have being very careful not to forget that marvellous marginal monosyllable &lsquo;Sic&rsquo; &hellip; <i>transition</i> is still swimming bravely across the seven seas, a wave a week. </div>
